f NJ and PA legislator John Kinsey (1693–1750) was one of the commissioners sent out from England in 1677 by the West Jersey proprietors to buy land from the Indians and to lay out a town. John was the leader of the Quaker party in the PA assembly and chief justice of the PA supreme court."]},{"name":"McKenzie","meanings":["Scottish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Coinnich</b>, a patronymic from the personal name <i>Coinneach</i> meaning ‘comely’, Anglicized as <i>Kenneth</i>. Compare the Irish form   McKinney   2. The Scottish spelling with <i>-z-</i> indicates palatalization of the <i>-n-</i> (compare   Menzies  ).","History: This is the name of a Scottish Highland clan, historically associated with the mountainous district of Kintail in nortwestern Scotland, with Cromarty, and with Loch Seaforth (Loch Shiphoirt) on the Island of Harris."]}]},{"name":"Iain","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Gaelic spelling of   Ian ."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Iain John MacKenzie 2nd Laird of Kintail was born in 1270, in Cromartyshire, Scotland, his father, Kenneth MacKenzie 1st Laird of Kintail, was 30 and his mother, Lady Morna MacDougall, was 26. He married Margaret de Strathbogie before 1294, in Ross-shire, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1328, in Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland, at the age of 58, and was buried in Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland."},"et":{"1270–1328":"1270–1328","1274–1328":"1274–1328","1300–1346":"1300–1346","1240–1304":"1240–1304","1244–1293":"1244–1293","1304":"1304","1346":"1346","1300":"1300","1244":"1244","about 1269":"umbes 1269","1274":"1274","1240":"1240","before 1294":"enne 1294","1293":"1293","1270":"1270","18 March 1293":"18. märts 1293","1328":"1328","Cromartyshire, Scotland":"Cromartyshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Kintail, Ross & Cromarty, Scotland":"Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland","Ross-shire, Scotland":"Ross-shire, Scotland","Cromartyshire, Highland, Scotland":"Cromartyshire, Scotland","Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland","Canterbury, Kent, England":"Canterbury, Kent, England"},"fi":{"1270–1328":"1270–1328","1274–1328":"1274–1328","1300–1346":"1300–1346","1240–1304":"1240–1304","1244–1293":"1244–1293","1304":"1304","1346":"1346","1300":"1300","1244":"1244","about 1269":"noin 1269","1274":"1274","1240":"1240","before 1294":"ennen vuotta 1294","1293":"1293","1270":"1270","18 March 1293":"18. maaliskuuta 1293","1328":"1328","Cromartyshire, Scotland":"Cromartyshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Kintail, Ross & Cromarty, Scotland":"Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland","Ross-shire, Scotland":"Ross-shire, Scotland","Cromartyshire, Highland, Scotland":"Cromartyshire, Scotland","Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland","Canterbury, Kent, England":"Canterbury, Kent, England"},"fr":{"1270–1328":"1270–1328","1274–1328":"1274–1328","1300–1346":"1300–1346","1240–1304":"1240–1304","1244–1293":"1244–1293","1304":"1304","1346":"1346","1300":"1300","1244":"1244","about 1269":"environ 1269","1274":"1274","1240":"1240","before 1294":"avant 1294","1293":"1293","1270":"1270","18 March 1293":"18 mars 1293","1328":"1328","Cromartyshire, Scotland":"Cromartyshire, Écosse","Scotland":"Écosse","Kintail, Ross & 